# ğŸŒŸ MoodTrack - Daily Wellness Companion

## ğŸ“‹ Project Overview

**MoodTrack** is a simple yet powerful MERN stack application that helps users track their daily moods, identify patterns, and build better mental wellness habits through journaling and visual insights.

---

## ğŸ¯ Problem Statement

Many people struggle to understand their emotional patterns and what triggers good or bad days. Traditional journaling is time-consuming, and most mood-tracking apps are overcomplicated or require premium subscriptions.

## ğŸ’¡ Solution

MoodTrack provides a clean, intuitive interface where users can:
- Log their daily mood with a single click
- Add optional journal entries
- View mood trends through visual charts
- Set daily wellness reminders
- Track mood triggers and patterns

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Tech Stack

**Frontend:**
- React.js (UI components)
- Tailwind CSS (styling)
- Recharts (data visualization)
- Axios (API calls)

**Backend:**
- Node.js + Express.js (server)
- MongoDB (database)
- JWT (authentication)
- Bcrypt (password hashing)

**Deployment:**
- Frontend: Vercel
- Backend: Render
- Database: MongoDB Atlas

---

## âœ¨ Core Features

### 1. User Authentication
- Secure signup/login with JWT
- Password encryption with Bcrypt
- Protected routes

### 2. Mood Logging
- Quick mood selection (5 emojis: ğŸ˜¢ ğŸ˜• ğŸ˜ ğŸ™‚ ğŸ˜„)
- Optional text journal entry
- Date and time stamping

### 3. Dashboard Analytics
- Weekly mood chart
- Monthly mood calendar view
- Mood streak counter
- Most common mood insights

### 4. Journal Archive
- View past entries
- Edit or delete entries
- Search by date or mood

### 5. Daily Reminders (Nice-to-have)
- Set custom reminder times
- Browser notifications

